HEADWORD: Thermifugine
<hw>Ther*mif"u*gine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ heat
+ L. <ets>fugere</ets> to flee.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An
artificial alkaloid of complex composition, resembling thalline and used
as an antipyretic, -- whence its name.</def>⟦br⟧
